---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Rent a Sound Meter"
  description="Borrow a calibrated Class 2 sound level meter for 7-14 days. You pay shipping only. Submit the form below to get started."
>

<article class="section">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <a href="/measure" class="text-brand-600 text-sm font-medium hover:text-brand-800 mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-1">
      &larr; Back to Measure
    </a>

    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900 leading-tight mb-4">
        Rent a Sound Meter
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-earth-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Borrow a calibrated Class 2 sound level meter. You pay shipping. We provide the equipment, the protocol, and the return label.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-16">
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="text-3xl font-display font-bold text-brand-600">$15&ndash;25</div>
        <p class="text-sm text-earth-500 mt-1">Round-trip shipping</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="text-3xl font-display font-bold text-brand-600">7&ndash;14</div>
        <p class="text-sm text-earth-500 mt-1">Day rental window</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="text-3xl font-display font-bold text-brand-600">Class 2</div>
        <p class="text-sm text-earth-500 mt-1">Calibrated annually</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white border border-earth-200 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900 mb-6">Request a Rental</h2>

      <form action="/api/rental/request" method="POST" class="space-y-5">
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
          <div>
            <label for="name" class="block text-sm font-medium text-earth-700 mb-1.5">Full Name *</label>
            <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required class="w-full rounded-lg border border-earth-300 px-4 py-2.5 text-earth-900 placeholder:text-earth-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-brand-500 focus:border-transparent" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label for="email" class="block text-sm font-medium text-earth-700 mb-1.5">Email *</label>
            <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required class="w-full rounded-lg border border-earth-300 px-4 py-2.5 text-earth-900 placeholder:text-earth-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-brand-500 focus:border-transparent" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <label for="address" class="block text-sm font-medium text-earth-700 mb-1.5">Shipping Address *</label>
          <textarea id="address" name="address" rows={3} required class="w-full rounded-lg border border-earth-300 px-4 py-2.5 text-earth-900 placeholder:text-earth-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-brand-500 focus:border-transparent resize-y" placeholder="Street, City, State, ZIP"></textarea>
        </div>

        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
          <div>
            <label for="start-date" class="block text-sm font-medium text-earth-700 mb-1.5">Preferred Start Date *</label>
            <input type="date" id="start-date" name="start_date" required class="w-full rounded-lg border border-earth-300 px-4 py-2.5 text-earth-900 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-brand-500 focus:border-transparent" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label for="end-date" class="block text-sm font-medium text-earth-700 mb-1.5">Preferred End Date *</label>
            <input type="date" id="end-date" name="end_date" required class="w-full rounded-lg border border-earth-300 px-4 py-2.5 text-earth-900 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-brand-500 focus:border-transparent" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <label for="intended-use" class="block text-sm font-medium text-earth-700 mb-1.5">How do you plan to use the meter? *</label>
          <textarea id="intended-use" name="intended_use" rows={2} required class="w-full rounded-lg border border-earth-300 px-4 py-2.5 text-earth-900 placeholder:text-earth-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-brand-500 focus:border-transparent resize-y" placeholder="Campaign name, HOA meeting, personal measurement, etc."></textarea>
        </div>

        <div>
          <label for="campaign" class="block text-sm font-medium text-earth-700 mb-1.5">Campaign (if applicable)</label>
          <input type="text" id="campaign" name="campaign" class="w-full rounded-lg border border-earth-300 px-4 py-2.5 text-earth-900 placeholder:text-earth-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-brand-500 focus:border-transparent" placeholder="Campaign name or leave blank" />
        </div>

        <div class="bg-earth-50 rounded-xl p-4 text-sm text-earth-600">
          <p class="font-medium text-earth-800 mb-1">What happens next?</p>
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-4 space-y-1">
            <li>Submit this form. We'll review and confirm availability within 48 hours.</li>
            <li>Once approved, you'll receive a payment link for shipping ($15&ndash;25).</li>
            <li>We'll ship the meter with the printed protocol and a prepaid return label.</li>
            <li>Use it for your rental window. We'll remind you 2 days before the return date.</li>
            <li>Upload your data at /measure/upload. Ship the meter back.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <input type="checkbox" id="terms" name="terms" required class="mt-1 rounded border-earth-300 text-brand-600 focus:ring-brand-500" />
          <label for="terms" class="text-sm text-earth-600">
            I understand this device is for advocacy use only. Measurements may not be admissible as legal evidence without independent verification. I accept the <a href="/terms" class="text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-800">rental terms of service</a>.
          </label>
        </div>

        <button type="submit" class="btn-primary w-full text-lg py-4">
          Submit Rental Request
        </button>
      </form>
    </div>

    <div class="prose mx-auto">
      <h2>About Our Rental Fleet</h2>
      <p>We maintain a lending library of 10&ndash;20 calibrated Class 2 sound level meters. Each meter is:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Calibrated annually by a certified calibration lab</li>
        <li>Shipped with the official measurement protocol and a quick-start guide</li>
        <li>Sanitized and tested between rentals</li>
        <li>Insured during shipping</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The rental program is the operationally heaviest part of the platform. We process requests within 48 hours and ship within 72 hours of payment. If your requested dates aren't available, we'll offer the closest alternative.</p>

      <h2>Costs</h2>
      <p>You pay only for shipping &mdash; typically $15&ndash;25 for round-trip with insurance. The meter rental itself is free. Our goal is to make it easy for anyone to collect good data, regardless of budget.</p>
      <p>If cost is a barrier, <a href="/contact">contact us</a>. We have a limited number of fully subsidized rentals available for campaigns in underserved communities.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>

</Layout>
